biolockj.module.r

Class BuildPvalHistograms

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.module.BioModuleImpl
      • biolockj.module.ScriptModuleImpl
        • biolockj.module.r.R_Module
          • biolockj.module.r.BuildPvalHistograms
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BioModule, ScriptModule

    public class BuildPvalHistograms
extends R_Module
implements ScriptModule
    This BioModule is used to build the R script used to generate p-value histograms for each report field and each taxonomy level configured.

      • rMainMethod

        protected String rMainMethod()
                      throws Exception
        The method returns R code for the function main(). For each taxonomy level - :
        1. Initialize a new 2x2 PDF report
        2. Read the parametric p-value spreadsheet
        3. Read the non-parametric p-value spreadsheet
        4. For each metadata field, add a parametric and non-parametric histogram

        Dependent BioLockJ Java-R methods called in this method:

        • PlotScript.FUNCTION_GET_PLOT_TITLE
        • rLinesInitPdf()
        • rMethodAddHistogram()
        • R_Module.rLinesReadStatsTable(String, String)
        • PlotScript.FUNCTION_PVAL_TEST_NAME
        • PlotScript.FUNCTION_GET_MAX_ATT_LEN
        Specified by:
        rMainMethod in class R_Module
        Returns:
        R code
        Throws:
        Exception - if Config property is missing or invalid

      • rMethodAddHistogram

        protected String rMethodAddHistogram()
        This method returns R code for the function addHistogram(v, title, xLabel, size).
        The histogram shows the distribution of vector values (v).

        R Function parameters:

        • v = Vector of data values used to build histogram
        • title = Histogram main value
        • xLabel = Histogram xlab value
        • size = Histogram cex.main value
        Returns:
        R code
